Knicks Name Former Hawks Coach Woodson as an Assistant on D’Antoni’s Staff

-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 
2011-08-29T15:32:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-29/knicks-name-former-hawks-coach-woodson-as-an-assistant-on-d-antoni-s-staff.html
The  New York Knicks  named former
Atlanta Hawks coach Mike Woodson as an assistant on  Mike
D’Antoni ’s coaching staff, the National Basketball Association
team said in a statement.  Woodson guided Atlanta to a regular-season record of 209
wins and 286 losses from 2004-2010.  Woodson, 53, was selected by the Knicks with the 12th
overall pick in the 1980 draft.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  